%S A394339 1,1,11,173,4753,198838,13457454,4207546916
%N A394339 Number of unlabeled posemigroups on n elements.
%C A394339 A posemigroup (partially ordered semigroup) is a triple (S, *, <=) where (S, <=) is a partial order, (S, *) is a semigroup (associative binary operation), and * is monotone with respect to <=: for all a, b, x in S, if a <= b then a*x <= b*x and x*a <= x*b.
%H A394339 Petr Gajdoš and Martin Kuřil, <a href="https://doi.org/10.1007/s00233-014-9602-3">Ordered semigroups of size at most 7 and linearly ordered semigroups of size at most 10</a>, Semigroup Forum, 89 (2014), 639-663.
%e A394339 a(0) = 0 for n = 0, the unique posemigroup is the empty structure which vacuously satisfies all axioms.
%Y A394339 Cf. A001035, A027851, A394338.
